Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?perf=20wave=2021=20patch=200092=20=E2=80=94=20L?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ever=20G:=20Tier-2=20audio=20config=20(11025=20mono,=20opt-in)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

DOS-PORT (patch 0092, Phase 9 wave 21 Lever G). Adds runtime audio
config selection via SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_TIER2=1 (strict-1, default
OFF). Tier-1 path (env unset) preserves patch-0061 behavior bit-
identical; Tier-2 opt-in flips to 11025 Hz mono with buffer pinned at
256 sample frames.

Mechanism (per docs/PHASE9-LEVER-G-PLAN.md § 1):
  Tier-1: 22050 stereo × 256-frame buffer ≈ 86 Hz IRQ rate, 11.6 ms
          latency. Per-IRQ data: 1024 B (256 × 2 × 2). Mix CPU: full.
  Tier-2: 11025 mono × 256-frame buffer ≈ 43 Hz IRQ rate, 23.2 ms
          latency. Per-IRQ data: 512 B (256 × 1 × 2). Mix CPU: ~half.

Halved IRQ rate IS the dominant Lever G mechanism. W20A2 ablation
showed audio interference is ~14 ms/flip baseline (~13 ms IRQ wall-
clock + audio mix). Halving IRQ rate predicts -6.5 ms/flip baseline
(hardware-deterministic; the IRQ rate IS halved when the buffer size
is held constant). Heavy-music mix-CPU savings range -3 to -22 ms/
flip per spec (mixer-implementation-dependent; measure in W21A iter).

Combined hypothesis: opening 25.6 → ~30-32 fps; heavy-music ~9 → ~12-
25 fps. Predictions framed as range per `perf_predictions_unreliable.md`.

Implementation (Path B per spec § 2.1):

1. SoundManager.h: replaced `#define SAMPLE_RATE 22050` with
   `extern uint32_t SAMPLE_RATE;` + new `extern uint32_t AUDIO_CHANNELS;`
   at global namespace scope (matches prior `#define` global-scope
   semantics; all consumers reference unqualified). Initial values
   (22050 / 2) preserve patch-0061 behavior. Updated header comment
   block to describe Tier-1 / Tier-2 runtime semantics + singleton-
   init ordering.

2. SoundManager.cpp:
   a. Defines both vars at TU global scope. Linkage: definition is
      here; other TUs see only extern decls.
   b. At top of SoundManager::init() (BEFORE MIX_CreateMixerDevice
      AND before any Pixtone/Organya singleton construction): read
      SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_TIER2; when "1", set SAMPLE_RATE=11025,
      AUDIO_CHANNELS=1, AND pin SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES
      to "256" via SDL_SetHintWithPriority(...,OVERRIDE).
   c. Buffer-pin is load-bearing (per spec § 2.3): without it, SDL3's
      heuristic preserves the ~11.6 ms latency target → would pick
      128 samples at 11025 mono → IRQ rate stays at ~86 Hz → the
      6.5 ms IRQ-rate-halving savings collapse. SDL_HINT_OVERRIDE
      ensures user-set SAMPLE_FRAMES doesn't accidentally un-pin.
   d. spec.channels = (int)::AUDIO_CHANNELS (was hard-coded 2).
   e. LOG_INFO line announces Tier-1 vs Tier-2 selection at startup
      with full mechanism prose for log-grep readability.

3. Pixtone.cpp: converts 8 hard-coded `2` channel sites to runtime
   `(int)::AUDIO_CHANNELS`. Sites:
   a. 501-502: paired src/dst SDL_AudioStream resample specs.
   b. 539: audio_spec for MIX_LoadRawAudioNoCopy on resampled buffer.
   c. 598-599: paired src/dst resample specs (mirror of 501-502).
   d. 629: audio_spec for resampled buffer (mirror of 539).
   e. 681 (was 672): master-chunk dst_spec (src stays at S8/1/22050
      = .pxt on-disk format per SoundManager.h:24-27 comment).
   f. 725 (was 710): audio_spec for master chunk's MIX_LoadRawAudio.

   NOTE: spec § 2.2 listed only 5 of these (501, 598, 672, 710 +
   Organya 476); audit found 4 additional sibling sites (502, 539,
   599, 629). Patched all 9 (Pixtone) + 1 (Organya) for correctness.
   Flagged to flush-instr in pre-format-patch DM — patching only the
   5 originally listed would produce broken mono playback (resample
   mismatch between src/dst channels at the missed sites).

4. Organya.cpp: line 476 converted to runtime AUDIO_CHANNELS.
   Organya synth's sampling_rate (line 187) already used SAMPLE_RATE
   so it auto-rescales at synth init.

5. docs/BOOT.md: new SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_TIER2 entry under
   "User-facing options" (NOT diagnostic — this is a hardware-tier
   config, not a debug flag). Documents the strict-1 match, audio
   quality trade, log-grep pattern, mechanism summary.

Singleton-init ordering verified:
- main.cpp:546 calls SoundManager::getInstance()->init() after
  SDL_Init + Renderer::init.
- SoundManager::init() runs the AUDIO_TIER2 env check FIRST (sets
  SAMPLE_RATE / AUDIO_CHANNELS), then MIX_CreateMixerDevice.
- Pixtone / Organya / Ogg singletons construct on first getInstance()
  from inside the SoundManager init flow — picks up runtime values.
- Pixtone.h:128's resampled_rate[NUM_RESAMPLED_BUFFERS] = {SAMPLE_RATE}
  in-class initializer evaluates at Pixtone object construction (post
  SoundManager::init in our init order), so it captures the runtime
  value, not the initial 22050.

Hot-path cost when AUDIO_TIER2 unset:
- Zero. The env check runs once at SoundManager::init.
- Subsequent code paths use the same SAMPLE_RATE / AUDIO_CHANNELS
  reads they used pre-0092 — just now via extern variable load
  instead of macro substitution. Single load per use, no functional
  difference. Tier-1 path is bit-identical to pre-0092.

OGG playback (if any user has OGG music installed): SDL3 OGG decoder
auto-resamples to whatever output rate is set. No manual changes
needed in Ogg.cpp. Confirmed per spec § 2.6.

No SDL-side patches expected. Mix_OpenAudio params are runtime-passed;
SDL3 audio device handles different rates/channels transparently. If
build-qa surfaces SDL3-DOS-at-11025-mono issues, sdl-engine investigates
in a separate patch — not pre-emptively patching SDL.

Test plan (subsequent W21A iter):
- Build-qa DOSBox-X smoke (3 configs):
  A. env-unset baseline (Tier-1; no behavior change).
  B. AUDIO_TIER2=1 (Tier-2 engaged; verify init log lines + audio
     plays without crash + 256-frame buffer pinned).
  C. AUDIO_TIER2=0 explicit (Tier-1 via killswitch path; same as A).
- Real-HW iter W21A (realhw): 2-PLAY ablation per spec § 5.
  - PLAY1 (W21A1): no AUDIO_TIER2 (Tier-1 baseline).
  - PLAY2 (W21A2): AUDIO_TIER2=1 (Tier-2 engaged).
  - Same FLIP_INSTR + DV+LFB compound config as W20A.
  - LOG_TAGs 5 chars (W21A1, W21A2) — fits 8.3.
- Audio quality A/B (operator subjective listening pass per spec § 4):
  title attract music, first-room ambient, SFX (gunshot/chime/dialogue),
  music+SFX overlap. Verdict: acceptable / borderline / unacceptable.
- 0093 default-flip (mirror 0086 → 0088 DIRECT_VESA pattern): post-
  W21A measurement + audio-quality validation, separate patch flips
  default to Tier-2 with `=0` killswitch reverting to Tier-1.

